He met her as she was leaving. She was wearing a black hat and holding flowers wrapped in a paper, on her way to a funeral. 'Your old partner is dead,' she said. 'Come with me.' Angry at not being allowed to warm himself, angry at the snow falling, and at the sentimental tears shining behind his aunt's veil, he turned sharply and wal